pouch boundary-line patch 0026 - CL-1b process lifecycle (posix_spawn/wait).

The Clade arc (docs/LLVM-DESIGN.md) sub-chunk CL-1b core: the process
substrate the toolchain drives -- the clang driver posix_spawns cc1/lld and
wait4s them; make/ninja fork-per-job over pipes. CL-0's census (16.1) found
the whole family (clone/execve/wait4/pipe2/dup3) is 0xFFFF ENOSYS. Each wires
onto an EXISTING kernel syscall -- ZERO new kernel surface.

Thylacine has NO fork/execve (a Proc cannot clone-and-replace its image);
SYS_SPAWN_FULL_ARGV(49) is the atomic spawn primitive, installing an explicit
positional fd_list (fd_list[i] -> child fd i, contiguous, lowest-free). So the
upstream posix_spawn (clone(CLONE_VM|CLONE_VFORK) -> run file_actions ->
execve) cannot apply: posix_spawn is rewritten to resolve its file_actions
STATICALLY into that fd_list (the dominant open/dup2-onto-0/1/2/close pattern
resolves to {0,1,2}), then call SYS_SPAWN_FULL_ARGV.

Wired (Linux name -> Thylacine kernel primitive):
  posix_spawn      -> SYS_SPAWN_FULL_ARGV (49)  [static file_actions resolve]
  posix_spawnp     -> PATH search (via /env) + posix_spawn
  waitpid / wait4  -> SYS_WAIT_PID (22)  [flag + status-word translation]
  pipe / pipe2     -> SYS_PIPE (8)       [2-register svc shim; rd=x0 wr=x1]

Two translations are load-bearing:
  * WAIT flags: kernel WAIT_CONTINUED is 4, Linux musl WCONTINUED is 8, and
    the kernel rejects unknown bits -- so the option word is mapped bit-by-bit.
  * WAIT status: a plain wait returns the RAW exit_status (0/1); musl's W*
    macros decode the Linux word, so it is repacked (raw & 0xff) << 8 ->
    WIFEXITED true, WEXITSTATUS == raw. A job-control wait already returns the
    Linux-packed word and is forwarded verbatim.

envp is inherited via the /env clone (the passed posix_spawn envp is a v1.x
lift the SYS_SPAWN_FULL_ARGV _pad_envp slot reserves). dup2/dup3 onto a chosen
target fd have NO kernel primitive (handle_dup is lowest-free only) and NO
runtime toolchain path needs one (posix_spawn resolves file_actions
statically) -- the onto-target case is a documented ENOSYS seam; old==new is a
validity check.

Files:
  src/internal/_pouch_process.h   NEW -- SYS_thyla_* numbers + the 96-byte
                                  sys_spawn_args mirror + shared decls.
  src/process/_pouch_process.c    NEW -- __pouch_pipe (2-reg svc shim) +
                                  __pouch_wait (flag + status translation).
  src/process/posix_spawn.c       rewrite -- static file_actions resolver.
  src/process/posix_spawnp.c      rewrite -- PATH search + posix_spawn.
  src/process/waitpid.c           -> __pouch_wait.
  src/linux/wait4.c               -> __pouch_wait (rusage zero-filled).
  src/unistd/dup2.c               old==new validate; onto-target ENOSYS.
  src/unistd/dup3.c               old==new EINVAL; onto-target ENOSYS.
  src/unistd/pipe.c               -> __pouch_pipe.
  src/unistd/pipe2.c              -> __pouch_pipe; O_CLOEXEC no-op.

